♪What's left to fear?♪

36
00:03:54,460 --> 00:03:55,460
- Drive!
- Yeah!

37
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:58,360
♪Wu wu wu♪

38
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:01,560
♪What's left to fear?♪

39
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:11,980
This is so weird.

40
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:13,820
That clam's completely mutated.

41
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,180
So aggressive.

42
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:16,260
With those tentacles.

43
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:18,060
And its shell's all jagged now.

44
00:04:18,060 --> 00:04:19,620
That was sinister.

45
00:04:20,580 --> 00:04:21,620
Seems this clam

46
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:22,780
- is no ordinary thing.
- It hurts?

47
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:24,460
Thought you were immune to pain.

48
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,740
Analyze this.

49
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:27,340
Could the relic of ill omen
be inside that clam?

50
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:30,220
From your description,

51
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,460
it has undergone
significant physiological changes.

52
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:33,860
Similar to how humans transform

53
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:35,780
when possessed
by the relic of ill omen.

54
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,020
High probability

55
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:39,180
the relic of ill omen
is within that clam.

56
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,300
Investigate further.

57
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:41,500
Understood.

58
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,020
I'll handle something now.

59
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:47,380
Done.

60
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,220
Mu Dai,

61
00:04:55,580 --> 00:04:56,900
have you noticed something?

62
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:57,900
What?

63
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,140
When I'm sitting,

64
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:01,100
I'm about as tall as you standing.

65
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:08,860
Master, Luo.

66
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:12,060
Why are you dressed like that?

67
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,260
My clothes have been washed.

68
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:16,860
I had to wrap myself in this blanket,

69
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:18,300
and Thirteen-Thousand
keeps yanking it off.

70
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,100
So annoying.

71
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,420
What's wrong?

72
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:21,740
I'm hungry.

73
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:26,860
Lucky this is solid ground.

74
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:27,740
That clam can't get here.

75
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:28,420
Right.

76
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,060
Are these ready?

77
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:30,740
Yeah.

78
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:31,580
Cao,

79
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:33,100
all you ever think about is food.

80
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,180
Look at you, coiled up like a razor clam

81
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:35,060
and still drooling for a meal.

82
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:35,780
Obviously!

83
00:05:35,780 --> 00:05:37,220
That clam's been tormenting me all day.

84
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,580
I'm eating its neighbors to vent.

85
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:41,300
Good?

86
00:05:41,460 --> 00:05:42,300
So good.

87
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:42,940
Try some.

88
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:44,260
- Luo Ren...
- Why's there shell?

89
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:44,860
Extra calcium.

90
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:46,740
Both of you, knock it off.

91
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,220
Luo Ren,

92
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:52,620
you really think the relic of ill omen

93
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:53,620
- is inside that cla...
- By the way,

94
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:55,300
what is the relic of ill omen?

95
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,940
That's too deep a question.

96
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:58,300
Answer mine first.

97
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:58,940
Master,

98
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,780
what have you been through these days?

99
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:01,500
How about this?

100
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:03,020
You explain

101
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:04,580
what we've been dealing with.

102
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:06,660
And you explain
what the relic of ill omen is.

103
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:07,620
You two,

104
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,540
take your skewers

105
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,620
and catch up over there.

106
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:11,620
Got it.

107
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:12,100
Wait.

108
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,100
Enough for you both?

109
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:15,580
Plenty.

110
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,420
Freak.

111
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:20,380
So what's your plan?

112
00:06:26,020 --> 00:06:27,860
You're not thinking
of taking that clam down, are you?

113
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:31,940
Luo Ren,

114
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:33,260
that's a clam,

115
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,380
not Pingting!

116
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,900
We could die.

117
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:40,260
Just so we're clear.

118
00:06:40,260 --> 00:06:41,260
I'm not getting involved in this.

119
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:43,540
I need to get back to the bar anyway.

120
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:45,820
I haven't figured it out yet.

121
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:48,500
Safety first, no matter what.

122
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:50,100
Tomorrow,

123
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,220
let's go check out those waters again.

124
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,100
We might find Hongsha's uncle.

125
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:57,740
Or...

126
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:01,460
Be careful.

127
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:02,860
That guy's back.

128
00:07:06,580 --> 00:07:08,020
Thirteen-Thousand, Thirteen-Thousand...

129
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:08,620
Let him go.

130
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,020
But after what happened yesterday...

131
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,100
He'll manage.

132
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:14,140
Fine.

133
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:21,020
Here. Your shrimp.

134
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,340
Gosh, it's burnt to a crisp.

135
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:25,940
Can we even eat it?

136
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:29,380
Thank you.

137
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,100
Delicious.

138
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,420
You're pretty skilled.

139
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:41,980
This counts as skilled?

140
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:44,540
It's a pity you haven't tried

141
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,300
my barbecue in Heisha.

142
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:47,620
Better?

143
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:49,460
You know

144
00:07:49,460 --> 00:07:50,580
how we grilled seafood back then?

145
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,620
We invented our own method,

146
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:55,020
Heisha stone-grilling.

147
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:56,620
Those seafood

148
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:58,180
were grilled on a large rock.

149
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:00,060
My colleagues and I

150
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:02,300
would sing and drink.

151
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:03,980
Those times

152
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:05,420
were really carefree.

153
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:07,260
Your colleagues?

154
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,100
I had two good friends.

155
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,100
One was Yuris.

156
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:17,820
He always enjoyed singing
those cheesy love songs.

157
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:22,260
Then there was

158
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,860
- Qingmu.
- Yuris, we can't hear you!

159
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:24,780
Louder!

160
00:08:24,780 --> 00:08:27,220
Back home, he had a fiancée.

161
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,900
Every night, he'd face the sea,

162
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,620
thinking about her.

163
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:33,300
That scene

164
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:34,740
is actually pretty sweet.

165
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:36,980
Where are they now?

166
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,420
Still in touch?

167
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:55,540
We haven't been in much contact

168
00:08:57,740 --> 00:08:58,860
after returning home.

169
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:04,620
Mu Dai,

170
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:06,220
we're heading
to the Eye of the Lake tomorrow.

171
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:07,460
Are you nervous?

172
00:09:08,980 --> 00:09:09,620
Yes.

173
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:11,740
Even with the gear and the car,

174
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,460
just thinking about that clam

175
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:15,260
makes my blood run cold.

176
00:09:18,460 --> 00:09:19,700
Let's play a game

177
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:21,020
to take your mind off it.

178
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:26,180
Rules are simple.

179
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:27,060
Heads or tails.

180
00:09:27,060 --> 00:09:28,900
Heads, you ask me a question.

181
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:31,020
Tails, I ask you one.

182
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:32,580
One question each.

183
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:33,260
Okay?

184
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:36,460
If he's not into it, then let it go.

185
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,140
Just ask him straight out.

186
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:40,260
Better than sitting here
stewing over it.

187
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,260
Don't torment yourself!

188
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,460
Here we go.

189
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:55,460
You're cheating.

190
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:59,260
Alright. Ask me.

191
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:00,340
Do you like me?

192
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:15,460
Mu Dai,

193
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:16,100
we...

194
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:17,060
Alright, I see.

195
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:19,860
Let's keep going.

196
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:29,940
Mu Dai,

197
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:36,940
if,

198
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:40,860
I mean, if

199
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:45,100
the guy you like

200
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:51,620
is in a huge,

201
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,140
huge mess,

202
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:00,900
would you still like him?

203
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:05,140
What are you trying to say?

204
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:07,140
I'm in a lot of trouble.

205
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,180
Life-threatening trouble.

206
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:16,740
So you mean

207
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:19,580
to avoid these troubles,

208
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,580
I should stay away from you?

209
00:11:22,380 --> 00:11:24,860
Or I should keep my distance
from you for now

210
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:25,860
and just wait

211
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:27,740
until you've sorted out

212
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:28,300
all these life-threatening

213
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:29,700
before we can be together?

214
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,380
You're dreaming.

215
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:41,060
I've never been in love before.

216
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:42,660
But I know

217
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:45,020
the best time for two people
to be together

218
00:11:45,260 --> 00:11:46,060
is when they

219
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,500
like each other.

220
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:49,340
All those excuses

221
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:51,100
like "Wait till I'm rich"

222
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,300
or "Wait till I've sorted out this"

223
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:53,820
just fade away as time goes by.

224
00:11:57,020 --> 00:11:58,140
I won't wait.

225
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:01,500
If two people don't seize
each other's hands

226
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:02,980
when they meet,

227
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:04,780
they might just go their separate ways

228
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:06,140
and hold someone else's hand.

229
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:08,900
I'll only wait for the kind...

230
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:11,700
The kind

231
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:16,100
where we've already developed
deep feelings for each other

232
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,580
and are willing to wait.

233
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:22,460
But we're

234
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:26,980
not there yet.

235
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:42,300
Mu Dai...

236
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:43,140
Enough.

237
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:45,100
I'm bringing Hongsha some food.

238
00:12:45,980 --> 00:12:47,940
Just consider that my question

239
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,700
was never asked.

240
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,820
We're still good friends.

241
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:02,940
Don't move!

242
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:05,140
You'd dive for clams now?

243
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:06,620
The God of Water will punish you!

244
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,380
Are you crazy?

245
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,780
But how can a crazy person
grow vegetables?

246
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,580
Or are you just crazy now and then?

247
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:16,660
Come here.

248
00:13:17,340 --> 00:13:18,540
Look at this.

249
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,140
Here.

250
00:13:19,740 --> 00:13:20,740
See clearly now.

251
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:22,700
They're all there.

252
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,380
So many

253
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,700
fighting over territory,

254
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:26,860
brawling.

255
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:28,500
Open your eyes

256
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,620
and take a good look!

257
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:50,860
Come on.

258
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:52,540
There.

259
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:57,100
There's a man over there.

260
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,220
See him?

261
00:13:58,860 --> 00:13:59,820
That's Jiang Zhao's father.

262
00:13:59,820 --> 00:14:00,660
Help... Help...

263
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:01,940
He's drowning.

264
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,780
He's watching you
and waiting for you to save him.

265
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,380
He's waiting for you to save him.

266
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:18,060
But you didn't. What held you back?

267
00:14:18,060 --> 00:14:19,580
No conscience left?

268
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:21,900
Do you think I don't know?

269
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:23,580
Over a decade!

270
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,940
Heaven judges me.

271
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:30,340
My own conscience condemns me!

272
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:35,060
I know I failed your father.

273
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:45,900
Mr. Jiang,

274
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,540
I'm sorry.

275
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,500
This is all my fault.

276
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,060
This is my retribution.

277
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:57,260
It has nothing to do with Jiang Zhao.

278
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:00,300
It's all my retribution!

279
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:02,380
Back then,

280
00:15:03,420 --> 00:15:06,380
my hesitation cost you your life.

281
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:09,900
I've lost my conscience

282
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,660
and made the God of Water mad.

283
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:17,420
Even our ancestors turned their backs.

284
00:15:17,660 --> 00:15:18,860
Now we

285
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:23,500
can't harvest a single clam.

286
00:15:23,820 --> 00:15:26,700
This is my reckoning!

287
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,380
Can't sleep either?

288
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,900
One minute I'm thinking about my uncle,

289
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:56,540
the next, that relic of ill omen
pops into my mind.

290
00:16:00,580 --> 00:16:01,340
I asked him.

291
00:16:03,820 --> 00:16:04,580
Asked what?

292
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,260
